org.isarnproject.sketches.java

Class TDigest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.isarnproject.sketches.java.TDigest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TDigest
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A t-digest sketch of sampled numeric data 
     Computing Extremely Accurate Quantiles Using t-Digests,
 Ted Dunning and Otmar Ertl,
 https://github.com/tdunning/t-digest/blob/master/docs/t-digest-paper/histo.pdf
 
     import org.isarnproject.sketches.java.TDigest;
 double[] data = // data that you would like to sketch
 TDigest sketch = TDigest.sketch(data)
 // the cumulative distribution function of the sketch; cdf(x) at x = 0
 double cdf = sketch.cdf(0.0)
 // inverse of the CDF, evaluated at q = 0.5
 double cdfi = sketch.cdfInverse(0.5)

      • K

        public static final double K
        The t-digest algorithm will re-cluster itself whenever its number of clusters exceeds (K/delta). This value is set such that the threshold is about 10x the heuristically expected number of clusters for the user-specified delta value. Generally the number of clusters will only trigger the corresponding re-clustering threshold when data are being presented in a non-random order.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • COMPRESSION_DEFAULT

        public static final double COMPRESSION_DEFAULT
        Default value for a t-digest compression (aka delta) parameter. The number of clusters varies, roughly, as about (50/delta), when data are presented in random order (it may grow larger if data are not presented randomly). The default corresponds to an expected number of clusters of about 100.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        public TDigest(double compression,

        compression - sketching compression setting. Higher = more compression. Must be > 0.

        maxDiscrete - maximum number of unique discrete values to track. Must be ≥ 0. If this number of values is exceeded, the sketch will begin to operate in normal continuous mode.
        sz - initial capacity to use for internal arrays. Must be > 0.

      • TDigest

        public TDigest(double compression,
               int maxDiscrete,
               double[] cent,
               double[] mass)
        Construct a t-digest from a list of cluster centers and masses. Object deserialization is one of the intended use cases for this constructor. NOTE: This constructor assumes the 'cent' and 'mass' arrays will be owned by the new t-digest object. If 'cent' and 'mass' are both null then an empty cluster will be created.
        Parameters:
        compression - sketching compression setting. Higher = more compression. Must be > 0.
        maxDiscrete - maximum number of unique discrete values to track. Must be ≥ 0. If this number of values is exceeded, the sketch will begin to operate in
        cent - the list of cluster centers. Assumed to be in sorted order. This array is assumed to be owned by the t-digest object after construction.
        mass - a list of cluster masses. Assumed to be parallel to centers. This array is assumed to be owned by the t-digest object after construction.

      • cdfInverse

        public final double cdfInverse(double q)
        Compute the inverse cumulative probability (inverse-CDF) for a quantile value, from the estimated probability distribution represented by this t-digest sketch.
        Parameters:
        q - a quantile value. The value of q is expected to be on interval [0, 1]
        Returns:
        the value x such that cdf(x) = q

      • cdfDiscreteInverse

        public final double cdfDiscreteInverse(double q)
        Compute the inverse cumulative probability (inverse-CDF) for a quantile value, from the estimated probability distribution represented by this t-digest sketch, assuming the sketch is "discrete" (e.g. if number of clusters ≤ maxDiscrete setting)
        Parameters:
        q - a quantile value. The value of q is expected to be on interval [0, 1]
        Returns:
        the smallest value x such that q ≤ cdf(x)
